WEBVTT

00:01.506 --> 00:10.377
For decades, people have used a specific statement to describe difficult times in life.

00:11.138 --> 00:14.162
And you've probably heard the statement before, but it goes like this.

00:15.204 --> 00:29.362
You are either coming out of a storm, you are in the middle of a storm, or you're about to go into a storm.

00:31.426 --> 00:35.211
And I don't know this morning which one of those categories you would fall into.

00:35.832 --> 00:41.260
Maybe you're like me and you just came out of a difficult time or a storm.

00:42.441 --> 00:46.807
Maybe where you sit this morning, you're walking through a crisis.

00:47.889 --> 00:50.693
And right now, you're in the middle of a storm.

00:51.694 --> 01:00.306
Or maybe for you, there's some stuff that's coming this week that you don't yet know about, but you're about to enter into a storm.

01:01.474 --> 01:04.999
All of us are familiar with the storms of life.

01:05.079 --> 01:14.752
And because of that, there's one common denominator, one thing that everybody in the room can relate with today.

01:17.276 --> 01:17.936
And that's pain.

01:20.200 --> 01:23.965
You see, we all can't relate with wealth because we all don't have wealth.

01:25.146 --> 01:30.834
We all can't relate with solid relationships because we all don't have solid relationships.

01:31.426 --> 01:41.659
We all can't relate with a great childhood or a nice car or a nice home or a certain passion or hobby because all of us don't have all those things.

01:42.740 --> 01:48.307
But every person in the room this morning knows what it is to struggle.

01:49.728 --> 01:51.010
You know what it is to hurt.

01:52.852 --> 01:57.918
You know what it is to feel sorrow and to walk through a difficult time.

01:59.841 --> 02:00.882
This month at Hope,

02:01.378 --> 02:07.307
We're talking about how to do that in a way that honors God.

02:08.409 --> 02:11.194
And we're learning from the life of a man named Daniel.

02:12.095 --> 02:14.980
Daniel was no stranger to difficult times.

02:15.661 --> 02:23.954
And if we had to take Daniel's whole life and boil it down to one succinct headline, here would be the headline.

02:25.396 --> 02:28.882
Faith in difficult times.

02:29.698 --> 02:35.203
And each week in this four part series, we're looking at a story from the Old Testament book of Daniel.

02:35.844 --> 02:41.169
The first week of this series, the first story we looked at was about Daniel and his three friends.

02:41.749 --> 02:49.457
And they were commanded to forsake their heritage and conform to a pagan lifestyle and culture.

02:50.257 --> 02:59.506
But as we saw in week one, God honored their faith and protected them even in the midst of a very difficult decision.

03:00.322 --> 03:06.350
And then last week in week two of this series, we looked at Daniel's three friends specifically.

03:07.031 --> 03:15.081
They were commanded to bow down and worship a large golden idol of the king and they refused.

03:15.161 --> 03:22.030
And we got to see God honored their faith as they were thrown into a fiery furnace to be burned alive.

03:22.891 --> 03:28.498
God protected them and brought them out healthy and okay.

03:29.442 --> 03:31.745
Well, this week we're going to look at another story.

03:32.506 --> 03:34.608
And this week's story is really special.

03:35.209 --> 03:41.857
This week's story involves Daniel, a king we're going to read about in a moment named Belshazzar.

03:42.838 --> 03:50.387
And this week's story involves God speaking in a very, very unique way.

03:51.088 --> 03:55.954
So if you have a copy of the scriptures, would you open it to Daniel chapter five?

03:56.546 --> 04:03.253
In just a moment, we're going to process through another story this morning from the Old Testament book of Daniel.

04:03.733 --> 04:05.895
Now, last week we were in Daniel chapter three.

04:06.696 --> 04:10.259
And since Daniel chapter three, a lot has happened.

04:10.900 --> 04:17.687
About 20 years have gone by and Daniel is now 82 years old.

04:18.588 --> 04:25.074
It's been 70 years since he was taken captive out of Judah and brought to Babylon.

04:25.858 --> 04:32.128
And at this point in his life, Daniel is no longer a prominent influential figure in the nation of Babylon.

04:32.148 --> 04:37.215
You see the king that we've studied the past few weeks, King Nebuchadnezzar, he has died.

04:37.856 --> 04:44.967
And when he passed away, all of the servants in his palace were sent out and sent to live in obscurity.

04:45.528 --> 04:47.711
So there's been a succession in the kingdom.

04:48.452 --> 04:52.178
And the king we're about to read about is a king named Belshazzar.

04:52.706 --> 05:00.237
and he is the second in command, and scholars tell us that he was King Nebuchadnezzar's grandson.

05:02.300 --> 05:09.091
So if you have a Bible, look in Daniel chapter five, and chapter five opens up by telling us about a party.

05:09.932 --> 05:16.081
King Belchaser is throwing a party in the palace, and it is a pagan party.

05:16.782 --> 05:22.130
The Bible says in the opening part of Daniel chapter five that they actually took some of the cups

05:22.338 --> 05:25.863
that were found in the temple of God and Judah they had stolen.

05:26.264 --> 05:32.393
And at this party, some of the people there are drinking wine out of those sacred, sacred cups.

05:32.934 --> 05:36.119
But not only that, they're worshiping idols.

05:36.399 --> 05:43.590
The Bible says that there was idol worship happening all throughout this party with thousands of people right there in the palace.

05:44.391 --> 05:51.442
And in the midst of this sinful pagan feast and party, God

05:52.034 --> 05:52.655
speaks.

05:53.936 --> 05:57.601
So look with me in Daniel chapter 5 starting in verse 5.

05:59.323 --> 06:12.759
Suddenly the fingers of a man's hand emerged and begin writing opposite the lampstand on the plaster of the wall of the king's palace.

06:13.981 --> 06:17.525
Just in case you didn't know that is not natural.

06:20.368 --> 06:21.650
And the king saw

06:21.858 --> 06:24.360
the back of the hand that did the writing.

06:25.501 --> 06:29.565
Then the king's face grew pale, I would say so.

06:30.786 --> 06:39.394
And his thoughts alarmed him and his hip joints went slack and his knees began knocking together.

06:40.015 --> 06:45.841
In other words, the king was losing it because the hand was riding on the wall.

06:46.501 --> 06:51.666
Verse seven, the king called aloud to bring in the conjurers

06:51.874 --> 07:13.522
the Chaldeans and the diviners, the king spoke and said to the wise men of Babylon, any man who can read this inscription and explain its interpretation to me, shall be clothed with purple and have a necklace of gold around his neck and have authority as third ruler in the kingdom.

07:14.363 --> 07:16.786
Then all the king's wise men came in.

07:17.154 --> 07:22.320
but they could not read the inscription or make known its interpretation to the king.

07:23.362 --> 07:26.646
Then King Belshazzar was greatly alarmed.

07:27.266 --> 07:33.995
His face grew even paler and the nobles were perplexed.

07:34.015 --> 07:37.960
So you get the scene of this week's story from Daniel chapter five.

07:38.781 --> 07:46.450
Huge party paganism sin is taking place and a hand appears and begins writing

07:46.882 --> 07:47.443
on the wall.

07:49.265 --> 07:56.395
Well, as everyone is standing there, probably with their jaws on the floor, the Bible goes on to say that the queen walked in.

07:56.435 --> 08:03.525
And most scholars believe this queen was King Bill Shazor's grandmother, the wife of King Nebuchadnezzar.

08:04.226 --> 08:07.911
And she sees that no one in the room understands the writing on the wall.

08:08.432 --> 08:12.658
So she says, there was a man who served King Nebuchadnezzar.

08:12.930 --> 08:19.058
And every time we had a difficult problem, this man had wisdom and insight.

08:19.619 --> 08:22.663
He was anointed and a man of God.

08:22.723 --> 08:24.065
His name was Daniel.

08:25.206 --> 08:33.858
King, I think we should find Daniel and bring him here to see if he can help us understand what this inscription actually says.

08:34.659 --> 08:36.541
So the king agreed, so they brought in Daniel.

08:37.743 --> 08:39.986
And the king says to Daniel, I've heard about you.

08:40.930 --> 08:43.093
You serve my grandfather well.

08:43.113 --> 08:46.859
I know that you're a man in which the spirit of the gods lives in.

08:46.879 --> 08:49.644
And he says, here's what I'll do for you, Daniel.

08:49.664 --> 08:56.695
If you will interpret the writing on the wall, I will make you the third in command in all of Babylon.

08:56.795 --> 09:00.500
I'll give you a robe and I'll give you a gold necklace.

09:00.520 --> 09:04.427
And then Daniel responds to the king after that offer.

09:05.128 --> 09:09.234
So look in your Bible, Daniel chapter five, verse 17.

09:09.506 --> 09:12.409
Here is Daniel's response.

09:12.429 --> 09:22.058
Then Daniel answered and said before the king, keep your gifts for yourself or give your rewards to someone else.

09:22.078 --> 09:27.803
However, I will read the inscription to the king and make the interpretation known to him.

09:28.864 --> 09:39.474
O king, the most high God granted sovereignty, grandeur, glory and majesty to Nebuchadnezzar, your father.

09:40.162 --> 09:41.043
or grandfather.

09:41.984 --> 10:01.187
Because of the grandeur which he bestowed on him, all the peoples, nations and men of every language feared and trembled before him, whomever he wished he killed and whomever he wished he spared alive and whomever he wished he elevated and whomever he wished he humbled.

10:01.868 --> 10:09.938
But when his heart was lifted up and his spirit became so proud that he behaved arrogantly, he was deposed

10:10.338 --> 10:14.022
from his royal throne and his glory was taken away from him.

10:16.244 --> 10:20.709
He was also driven away from mankind and his heart was made like that of beasts.

10:21.269 --> 10:24.352
In his dwelling place was with the wild donkeys.

10:24.412 --> 10:37.746
He was given grass to eat like cattle and his body was drenched with the dew of heaven until he recognized that the Most High God is ruler over the realm of mankind and that he sets over it whomever

10:37.986 --> 10:38.507
He wishes.

10:38.607 --> 10:40.369
That's what happened to King Nebuchadnezzar.

10:41.109 --> 10:54.624
Then he says in verse 22, yet you, his son, Belchaser, have not humbled your heart, even though you knew all of this, but you have exalted yourself against the Lord of heaven.

10:55.305 --> 11:03.794
And they have brought the vessels of his house before you and you and your nobles and your wives and your concubines have been drinking wine from them.

11:04.226 --> 11:11.495
And you have praised the gods of silver and gold, of bronze, iron, wood, and stone, which do not see, hear, or understand.

11:12.035 --> 11:19.625
But the God in whose hand are your life, breath, and all your ways, you have not glorified.

11:20.325 --> 11:23.870
Then the hand was sent from him, and this inscription was written out.

11:23.950 --> 11:25.892
Now, this is the inscription that was written out.

11:26.533 --> 11:30.157
Manet, Manet, Tekel, Uparsen.

11:30.878 --> 11:33.641
This is the interpretation of the message.

11:33.661 --> 11:34.162
Manet.

11:34.946 --> 11:39.476
God has numbered your kingdom and put it to an end.

11:41.079 --> 11:46.350
To Cal, you have been weighed on the scales and found deficient.

11:47.613 --> 11:53.746
Perez, your kingdom has been divided and given over to the Medes and Persians.

11:54.210 --> 12:05.567
Then Belshazzar gave orders and they clothed Daniel with purple and put a necklace of gold around his neck and issued a proclamation concerning him that he now had authority as the third ruler in the kingdom.

12:06.248 --> 12:10.595
That same night, Belshazzar the Chaldean king was slain.

12:11.476 --> 12:15.702
So Darius the maid received the kingdom at about the age of 62.

12:18.446 --> 12:23.474
And with verse 30 and 31, this dominant empire,

12:23.714 --> 12:28.600
called Babylon, came collapsing down.

12:30.061 --> 12:32.464
Now here's what's interesting about this week's story.

12:33.545 --> 12:40.733
What's interesting is that Daniel is not necessarily the one who is caught in a difficult time.

12:41.955 --> 12:49.443
Now he walked into a pretty tense room, but Daniel was not the one in this situation who was walking through a difficult time.

12:50.404 --> 12:51.826
And I'm sure you can relate

12:52.194 --> 12:58.381
There are times in your life when the difficult time you're a part of is not your difficult time.

12:59.463 --> 13:08.814
Because of a relationship, because of an opportunity, you can be invited into someone else's difficult time in order to help.

13:10.015 --> 13:14.761
So here's the question I want us to wrestle with as we look at this text this morning.

13:15.822 --> 13:22.130
How do I help others who are walking through

13:22.786 --> 13:23.367
a crisis.

13:25.249 --> 13:30.295
All of us can relate with being invited into some crisis and not really knowing what to do.

13:30.335 --> 13:40.667
What are the principles in this story that we can pull out this morning to understand how we help others who are walking through a difficult time?

13:41.448 --> 13:49.458
One of the things that's very fascinating is that Daniel would even be invited into this circumstance in the first place.

13:49.890 --> 13:51.292
He's 82 years old.

13:51.592 --> 13:52.534
He's retired.

13:52.894 --> 13:55.418
He's not been in the palace for a long time.

13:56.139 --> 14:03.009
What is it about Daniel that made his name come up whenever a crisis arose in the kingdom?

14:03.029 --> 14:05.613
Well, I want to start by giving you an application statement.

14:06.193 --> 14:13.664
And then I want us to look at two characteristics of a godly person who is invited to help during a crisis.

14:14.325 --> 14:17.810
Here's the application statement I want us to unpack for a few moments this morning.

14:18.594 --> 14:29.188
Trusting God in my crisis allows me to help others through their crisis.

14:30.630 --> 14:37.419
Trusting God in my crisis allows me to help others through their crisis.

14:38.060 --> 14:44.889
We've been talking for the past few weeks about the personal storms, the personal tough times that you're walking through.

14:45.610 --> 14:48.594
As you've thought about those, both past and present,

14:49.154 --> 14:57.603
Can you honestly say today that through those times, you continued to trust God?

15:01.427 --> 15:04.150
The word trust is a word that we throw around quite a bit.

15:04.991 --> 15:12.439
If you were to look it up in the dictionary, the word trust means to have confidence, faith or hope in someone or something.

15:13.240 --> 15:19.026
It means reliance on the strength or ability of a person

15:19.490 --> 15:19.911
or think.

15:21.193 --> 15:28.024
And this morning, as we think about trusting God, I want to give you a biblical definition of trust.

15:28.845 --> 15:29.226
Here it is.

15:29.266 --> 15:43.890
To depend with confidence on the character, ability, strength, and truth of God for everything in my

15:45.730 --> 16:02.613
I want us to read that out loud together this morning off the screen on three, one, two, three, to depend with confidence on the character, ability, strength, and truth of God for everything in my life.

16:03.715 --> 16:12.046
I want to ask you again, as you think about the difficult days you've walked through, both past and present, have you trusted God?

16:13.208 --> 16:14.930
Have you remained confident

16:15.810 --> 16:19.374
on his strength, on his character, on his ability, and on his truth.

16:20.335 --> 16:33.970
In my life, some of the major storms I've walked through have been cancer and a miscarriage that my wife had, losing a loved one either because of a severed relationship or because they left Earth and entered into eternity.

16:34.270 --> 16:42.159
And I'm thankful that in all those moments, even though I asked some really, really hard questions and it was hard, I continued to trust God.

16:43.240 --> 16:45.202
And that was the case for Daniel as well.

16:45.474 --> 16:59.372
Regardless of the circumstance we see him in throughout the book of Daniel, he continued to have confidence on the character, strength, ability, and truth of his heavenly Father.

16:59.693 --> 17:07.263
So much so that after he'd retired from the kingdom, when a crisis arose, he's invited in.

17:07.403 --> 17:08.084
Why is that?

17:08.784 --> 17:13.010
Because of the way he trusted God during his personal storms,

17:13.634 --> 17:19.100
He was invited in to help others when they walk through their storms.

17:20.882 --> 17:22.044
Here's how that applies to us.

17:23.085 --> 17:35.760
When we remain faithful through the storms of life, it creates opportunities for us to help others as they walk through difficult times.

17:36.901 --> 17:41.266
That's why trusting God in the midst of your crisis is so important.

17:42.146 --> 17:44.409
Maybe you're here today and you're about to give up.

17:45.029 --> 17:47.572
You're just on the brink of saying, forget it all.

17:48.133 --> 17:48.714
Don't give up.

17:49.735 --> 18:00.347
If you continue to trust God in the midst of your crisis, later on down the road, you're gonna be able to help others as they walk through their crisis.

18:02.129 --> 18:09.938
The Bible says that after the hand finished riding on the wall, and I don't even know what that looked like, but the queen said,

18:10.050 --> 18:11.511
Look, nobody knows what to do.

18:11.572 --> 18:13.033
You should call on Daniel.

18:13.534 --> 18:18.158
And I love what the Bible says here in verses 13 and 14 of Daniel chapter five.

18:18.819 --> 18:21.321
It says, then Daniel was brought in before the king.

18:21.982 --> 18:24.565
The king spoke and said to Daniel, I love this.

18:25.446 --> 18:26.767
Are you that Daniel?

18:29.570 --> 18:34.695
Who is one of the exiles from Judah, whom my father, the king brought from Judah.

18:35.356 --> 18:37.778
Now I have heard about you.

18:38.402 --> 18:46.472
that a spirit of the gods is in you, and that illumination, insight, and extraordinary wisdom have been found in you.

18:47.353 --> 18:49.956
There are a couple of really powerful phrases in these verses.

18:50.577 --> 18:52.099
He says, are you that Daniel?

18:52.840 --> 19:01.931
You see, Daniel had a reputation of being a man of faith who had been used by God in difficult circumstances.

19:02.571 --> 19:03.513
He was that Daniel.

19:04.193 --> 19:08.018
And then the king says, I have heard about you.

19:08.866 --> 19:09.547
Here's the point.

19:10.728 --> 19:13.411
He did not hear about what Daniel said.

19:13.471 --> 19:17.194
He heard about what Daniel did.

19:17.214 --> 19:28.265
I love what the Bible says in 1 Corinthians, chapter four, it says, for the kingdom of God is not just a lot of talk.

19:30.528 --> 19:34.191
It is living by God's power.

19:36.133 --> 19:36.914
And here's what I know.

19:38.210 --> 19:49.310
your lifestyle, your lifestyle of faith will say more to the world than anything that ever comes out of your mouth.

19:51.635 --> 19:57.746
You see, what was so impressive to these people about Daniel was not the stuff that was coming out of his mouth.

19:58.178 --> 20:03.445
It was the fact that they had seen God use him in some very difficult situations.

20:03.565 --> 20:12.216
And because Daniel trusted God in his personal storms, he was able to help others to walk through their storms.

20:13.558 --> 20:17.523
There are certain things about every person that leave a lasting impression.

20:18.645 --> 20:21.008
And it's not a real long list, but there are numerous things.

20:21.128 --> 20:22.610
One of those things is attitude.

20:23.266 --> 20:28.431
The way you view life and the way you treat people leaves a lasting impression.

20:29.592 --> 20:34.497
But something else that leaves a lasting impression is our response to tragedy.

20:35.798 --> 20:38.480
No one wants to know what life is like when things are good.

20:38.540 --> 20:43.405
They want to know what we do when we walk through a struggle.

20:44.946 --> 20:45.767
Let me give you an example.

20:46.768 --> 20:53.074
This Thursday will mark one year since our entire campus was flooded

20:53.698 --> 20:56.741
due to some heavy rain here in our part of the city.

20:57.642 --> 20:58.723
Some of you may remember that.

20:58.783 --> 21:00.265
Some of you may not remember that to me.

21:00.405 --> 21:01.426
It was like it was yesterday.

21:02.147 --> 21:04.550
I was standing right there with water up to my ankles.

21:06.212 --> 21:15.281
And in that moment, the news camera started showing up and people from the neighborhood started flooding the campus, one to help, but another just to see what was going on.

21:15.441 --> 21:19.666
I believe they wanted to see our response to the tragedy.

21:20.962 --> 21:30.571
And we were able to process through that and hundreds of people from our church showed up with brooms and squeegees to get all the water out of the building and to help clean off the campus.

21:31.031 --> 21:39.279
And from that point, I can't tell you the number of people who have talked to me and said, oh, you go to that church.

21:40.921 --> 21:44.764
The church that flooded and everybody who goes there showed up to serve.

21:45.645 --> 21:48.308
I said, yeah, that's my church.

21:48.328 --> 21:49.068
Here's the reality.

21:49.429 --> 21:50.770
Nobody showed up.

21:50.882 --> 21:56.047
for the grand opening when we cut the ribbon, but everybody showed up when the place flooded.

21:58.049 --> 22:04.355
The way that we respond to tragedy, the way that we respond to difficult times is so important.

22:05.116 --> 22:19.570
And Daniel is an example that if we respond to difficult times in the right way, it will create a platform from which we can have opportunities to speak into the lives of people.

22:21.090 --> 22:26.677
There will be believers and non-believers in your life who watch you walk through a tragedy.

22:28.079 --> 22:36.650
And based off the way you respond, they may choose to invite you into their life when you walk through a tragedy.

22:37.491 --> 22:45.161
Your response in the past may be exactly what God wants to use to speak to someone else when they're walking through a crisis.

22:46.223 --> 22:48.946
So let me ask you this evaluation question about your life.

22:49.858 --> 22:56.207
Do people come to you for help when they are facing a crisis?

22:56.227 --> 23:11.809
In other words, are you that person, the person in your circle of influence that they know, whether it's a good day or a bad day, you're someone who trusts God and they can come to you in the midst of their crisis.

23:13.251 --> 23:18.098
You see what you learn when you go through a difficult time is not just for you.

23:20.322 --> 23:21.684
It's for other people as well.

23:24.287 --> 23:33.898
Some of the things you've learned, some of the things that God has taught you through the midst of the storm can be leveraged as you're given an opportunity to speak into the lives of others.

23:33.918 --> 23:35.580
And if you're here today and you would say, you know what?

23:36.261 --> 23:37.643
Nobody's really asking me.

23:39.485 --> 23:44.451
Nobody's really inviting me in during a crisis to help or to serve.

23:45.452 --> 23:46.994
Well, I believe that's a reflection.

23:47.234 --> 23:50.178
on the way you've been trusting God in the midst of your personal crisis.

23:51.060 --> 24:01.114
Because as we see from the life of Daniel, trusting God in my crisis allows me to help others through their crisis.

24:02.136 --> 24:04.940
I want to give you a couple of just applications today.

24:05.000 --> 24:11.229
So I want to share two characteristics of a godly person who's invited into a crisis.

24:12.170 --> 24:14.834
This week someone may call you and say, I need help.

24:15.074 --> 24:17.758
and you find yourself in the middle of the crisis.

24:18.159 --> 24:23.548
What are the things that should be a priority for you if you're really seeking to help others?

24:23.989 --> 24:25.291
Here's the first characteristic.

24:27.054 --> 24:28.957
They speak the truth.

24:30.219 --> 24:38.272
When a godly person is invited into a crisis, one of their priorities is that they speak the truth.

24:39.033 --> 24:42.098
I love Daniel's response to the king in verse 17.

24:42.562 --> 24:51.373
He says, then Daniel answered and said before the king, keep your gifts for yourself or give your rewards to someone else.

24:51.953 --> 24:57.800
However, I will read the inscription to the king and make the interpretation known to him.

24:57.900 --> 25:01.144
In essence, Daniel says, listen, your gifts don't matter.

25:02.085 --> 25:10.736
What matters is what's on that wall because that's the truth of God given to every person in this room.

25:10.756 --> 25:12.498
That was Daniel's priority.

25:12.866 --> 25:19.975
And as you move into moments of crisis where you seek to help, speaking the truth must be a priority.

25:19.995 --> 25:26.543
And here's why, because only the truth sets people free.

25:28.986 --> 25:32.470
Only the truth sets people free.

25:33.391 --> 25:42.002
In the midst of chaos and emotion of a situation that is in crisis, there is no substitute

25:42.242 --> 25:43.283
for the truth of God.

25:44.385 --> 25:50.713
Believe it or not, what people need in a moment of crisis is not your opinion.

25:52.195 --> 26:02.228
They need to know there is a God who cares, there is a God who is in control, and there is a God who is building a kingdom that will never be shaken.

26:02.829 --> 26:04.792
I love what the Bible says in John chapter eight.

26:05.492 --> 26:09.778
It says, so Jesus was saying to those Jews who had believed Him.

26:10.114 --> 26:19.807
If you continue in my word, then you are truly disciples of mine and you will know the truth and the truth will make you free.

26:21.789 --> 26:34.566
Jesus is telling us if we want to see people set free, if we want to be free people, we will never experience that apart from the truth.

26:36.028 --> 26:37.330
So let me ask you a question.

26:38.370 --> 26:45.060
When people come to you during a crisis, do you point them to God?

26:48.025 --> 26:54.495
When you walk into a crisis, when people come to you, are you someone who wants to shine light on what you think?

26:55.216 --> 26:58.741
Are you someone who wants to shine light on your heavenly Father?

26:59.362 --> 27:04.530
When they come to you during a moment of crisis, do you point them to Him?

27:05.410 --> 27:13.220
because one characteristic of a godly person who's invited into a crisis is that they speak the truth.

27:13.920 --> 27:27.938
We see it in the life of Daniel and we could probably list example after example across the room that you are standing on the truth of God when you've been invited in to help during a crisis.

27:30.020 --> 27:31.602
Here's a second characteristic.

27:32.738 --> 27:35.681
of a godly person who's invited into a crisis.

27:37.142 --> 27:40.285
They demonstrate grace.

27:42.547 --> 27:46.831
This week in our teaching team, we kind of had a holy moment.

27:48.313 --> 27:52.477
We were just reading over the scriptures, praying over the scriptures, discussing the scriptures.

27:53.438 --> 28:02.226
And we begin to see just how much of God's gracious pursuit of humanity

28:02.978 --> 28:05.501
is in this passage.

28:05.521 --> 28:06.402
Let me tell you what I mean.

28:07.824 --> 28:14.252
In verses 22 to 23, here are some of the things that Daniel says about the king, Bill Shazzar.

28:15.273 --> 28:17.877
He says, you have not humbled your heart.

28:19.338 --> 28:21.541
You have exalted yourself.

28:22.943 --> 28:31.954
You have praised others, others so-called gods, and the God in whose hand is your life breath, you

28:32.098 --> 28:34.221
have not glorified.

28:35.442 --> 28:40.388
I would imagine what he said to the king was true for the other thousand people who were in the room.

28:41.209 --> 28:46.135
And automatically when I read those things in those verses about the king, here's what I think.

28:47.157 --> 28:54.025
Him, nor his palace, did not be, did not deserved to be pursued by God.

28:56.408 --> 29:01.074
There was no one in this palace who deserved to be pursued by God.

29:01.570 --> 29:05.396
They did not deserve his time, his attention, nor his love.

29:06.197 --> 29:07.919
But then here's the part that's so convicting.

29:10.363 --> 29:10.964
Neither do I.

29:14.109 --> 29:15.230
And honestly, neither do you.

29:17.594 --> 29:20.558
What should have happened in this story is that God just wipes out the kingdom.

29:21.600 --> 29:26.287
There's no hand, there's no messenger in Daniel, there's no second opportunity.

29:26.948 --> 29:28.370
I mean, they're doing some pretty

29:28.578 --> 29:30.221
awful stuff at this party.

29:30.261 --> 29:31.823
They should have just been wiped out.

29:32.124 --> 29:43.843
God should not have given them a second thought, but in His grace, He chose to give them multiple messages to show His pursuit of them.

29:43.904 --> 29:50.194
And as we read this story in 2013, we have to read it from the context of the cross.

29:50.914 --> 29:52.737
You see, we're on the other side of the cross.

29:52.777 --> 30:01.852
So we know that even throughout history, God has had a plan of redemption through which he is seeking to redeem the human race.

30:06.759 --> 30:18.418
Here's why demonstrating grace is so important for you and for me as we walk into a crisis because God graciously pursues us.

30:19.458 --> 30:22.844
even when we are not pursuing him.

30:25.949 --> 30:27.833
You know, the Bible says what happens to the king.

30:27.913 --> 30:28.774
He died that night.

30:29.716 --> 30:33.743
But what we don't know is what happened to the other thousands of people that were in the room.

30:35.586 --> 30:37.109
They saw the handwriting on the wall.

30:37.169 --> 30:39.332
They saw Daniel's message.

30:39.393 --> 30:44.882
They saw the kingdom that they thought could never be destroyed fall down and collapse forever.

30:46.274 --> 30:53.442
Even in that moment, God was pursuing them even though they were not pursuing him.

30:55.024 --> 31:00.731
You see, God pursues us because he loves us, not because we deserve it.

31:04.014 --> 31:12.344
There's a passage of scripture in the book of Ephesians that really, it's just humbling to read and to process, but it's in Ephesians chapter two.

31:13.065 --> 31:14.226
And here's what the Bible says.

31:15.522 --> 31:30.844
And you were dead, and your trespasses and sins, in which you formally walked according to the course of this world, according to the prince of the power of the heir, of the spirit that is now working in the sons of disobedience.

31:30.865 --> 31:42.802
Among them, we too all formally lived in the lusts of our flesh, indulging the desires of the flesh and of the mind, and were by nature children of wrath, even as the rest.

31:43.650 --> 31:45.812
meaning we did not deserve to be pursued.

31:46.793 --> 32:03.990
Verse four, but God being rich in mercy, because of his great love with which he loved us, even when we were dead in our trespasses, made us alive together with Christ and raised us up with him and seated us with him in the heavenly places in Christ Jesus.

32:04.591 --> 32:11.698
So that in the ages to come, he might show the surpassing riches of his grace and kindness towards us in Christ Jesus.

32:12.674 --> 32:21.608
For by grace you have been saved through faith and that not of yourselves, it is the gift of God, not as a result of work so that no one may boast.

32:22.250 --> 32:33.267
For we are His workmanship created in Christ Jesus for good works which God prepared beforehand so that we would walk in them.

32:33.287 --> 32:39.858
God graciously pursues us even when we are not pursuing.

32:41.922 --> 32:42.843
Let me ask you a question.

32:44.445 --> 32:48.451
Are you as gracious with others as God is with you?

32:53.818 --> 33:01.027
When you're invited into a crisis, are you as gracious with others as God is with you?

33:02.469 --> 33:09.298
I really struggle with that, but one of the things that God has just taught me is there's nothing that someone will do to me

33:10.082 --> 33:14.789
that I haven't done a hundred times to Jesus.

33:14.809 --> 33:22.100
I know across this room, there are probably a lot of stories of stuff you might be right in the middle of.

33:22.140 --> 33:24.824
It's not your difficult time, but you've been invited into it.

33:25.525 --> 33:30.973
And maybe one of the reasons that you're in it is because you have been faithful in your personal storms.

33:31.574 --> 33:36.341
And now you have a platform to help others walk through their storms.

33:37.443 --> 33:39.826
As you walk through that, let me encourage you.

33:40.738 --> 33:41.579
Speak the truth.

33:43.261 --> 33:51.729
Stand upon the foundational truth of scripture in the midst of all the moving parts and all the chaos and demonstrate grace.

33:53.050 --> 34:01.819
There may be some people you need to cry with, people you need to pray with, people you need to walk with, even though it's difficult.

34:03.501 --> 34:08.626
As we prepare to respond to the word today, there are really two groups of people here.

34:09.794 --> 34:14.341
There are some of us who need to give grace and truth.

34:15.944 --> 34:25.759
You're walking through a circumstance right now and you know the next thing you need to give energy to is giving truth and grace to the people that you're walking with.

34:25.799 --> 34:38.258
And if that's you, let me encourage you to demonstrate the same patience and wisdom and love and compassion to those people that God has demonstrated to you and just walk with them.

34:38.882 --> 34:45.372
I pray that God would use you because of what He's taught you in the past to speak to them in the midst of their storm.

34:45.432 --> 34:52.984
And in just a moment, when we stand to respond, you may want to go to somebody in this room that you know is struggling and just pray for them.

34:54.146 --> 35:02.038
Maybe you know somebody's walking through a storm and you want to walk over and just pray the truth of Scripture over them and demonstrate grace in their life.

35:02.098 --> 35:04.402
Maybe you want to come forward and just get on this altar.

35:04.642 --> 35:07.547
and just pray for them, intercede on their behalf.

35:07.587 --> 35:10.151
We had numerous people do that in the last service.

35:11.933 --> 35:13.376
But maybe you're not in that group.

35:14.177 --> 35:16.961
Maybe you're not someone who needs to give truth and grace.

35:17.802 --> 35:23.632
Maybe you're here this morning and you need to receive truth and grace.

35:26.376 --> 35:32.946
You realize this morning that just as God pursued these Babylonians, that he's pursuing you,

35:34.658 --> 35:36.060
He's pursued you through his son.

35:36.121 --> 35:37.964
He's pursued you through the cross.

35:38.405 --> 35:41.470
He's pursued you by bringing you to this service today.

35:42.252 --> 35:48.743
Maybe you've had a knowledge of God your whole life, but you've never had a moment when you confess your sin before him.

35:49.264 --> 35:57.138
Acknowledge that he is the way, the truth, and the life and invited him to save you and forgive you of your sins for eternity.

35:57.826 --> 36:01.215
When we stand up in just a moment, we're going to have some of our pastors here at the front.

36:01.656 --> 36:08.914
We would love to share with you how you can be saved and how you can come into a relationship with God.

